ce:section.ce:para:
To explore molecular mechanisms underlying the effect of CDs on C. pyrenoidosa under high-intensity light stress, transcriptome analysis was conducted to identify differentially expressed genes (DEGs) between the high-intensity light stress (CK) and high-intensity light stress with 40 mg/L of CDs treatment (CDs). Spearman’s Correlation Coefficient analysis among various sample pairs unequivocally demonstrates the reliability and strong reproducibility of each sample ( Fig. S8
). The statistical data of the C. pyrenoidosa transcriptome are shown in Table S2 , with a cumulative total of 479,365,440 reads derived from the analysis of six cDNA libraries. After removing low-quality reads of C. pyrenoidosa, 225,121,398 (CK) and 254,010,918 (CDs) clean reads were obtained, with Q20 > 96.8 % and Q30 > 92.0 %. These results indicate that the transcriptome sequencing data are suitable for further analysis. Based on RNA transcriptome sequencing analysis, a total of 751 DEGs were identified between the CK and CDs groups, with 539 genes significantly up-regulated and 212 genes significantly down-regulated (fold change > 2, q value < 0.05. ( Fig. S9
).
